[1] Pakistan: H1N1
Date: Mon 21 Dec 2015
Source: anonymous [edited]


There are 4 confirmed H1N1 patients at Shifa International Hospital Islamabad, 1 at CMH [Combined Military Hospital] Rawalpindi and 2 at POF Hospital Wah. 1 at POF hospital Wah Rawalpindi has expired. With the upsurge of cold in some areas of Pakistan, cases of respiratory tract infections are on rise. In response to the request for information by ProMED-mail regarding the rise of ARI [acute respiratory infection] cases in Rawalpindi [Punjab province], a team of epidemiologists also visited the twin hospitals in Rawalpindi and conducted a survey in paediatric wards. The condition seems to be normal as compared to previous years data during cold months.

1) 7 samples of H1N1 pdm09 have been confirmed out of 10 samples received from Bacha Khan Medical Complex Swabi [Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province] in last 15 days. Samples have been confirmed by NIH [National Institute of Health] Islamabad. All the cases are stable and are under treatment. Infectious disease specialist Dr Amjad is treating all the cases.

2) 3 cases of H1N1 pdm09 have been confirmed from Shifa International Hospital Islamabad. Two of them are critical and are in medical ICU. Contacts have been listed and are under observation.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[On 6 Dec 2015, ProMED-mail reported a serious influenza outbreak in the Swabi district of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, Pakistan, with 8 of 13 cases identified as H1N1 (Influenza - Pakistan: (KP) (H1N1)pdm09 20151206.3843544). - Mod.LK]

