[These cases are most likely influenza A(H1N1)pdm09 virus (pH1N1). H1N1 was 1st detected in 2009 when it was called "swine flu" because the virus was similar to viruses found in pigs. From 2009-2010, this virus caused a pandemic that claimed several hundred lives. The H1N1 virus is currently a seasonal flu virus found in humans. The virus can spread from human to human. Symptoms of swine flu in people are similar to the symptoms of regular human flu and include fever, cough, sore throat, body aches, headache, chills and fatigue.

A map of Pakistan can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3885143,140.

Maps of China can be found at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3885143,361.

